30	// US-046 — Submission composer. Canonical creator-side entry to the
31	// submit-video edge function (US-045). Fetches the single-application
32	// context via the get_my_application_for_submit SECURITY DEFINER RPC
33	// so we see the pinned listing_version_id's POST conditions and the
34	// lister handle even if the listing has since been paused or closed
35	// (listing_conditions RLS is gated on listing.status='active').
36	//
37	// The story AC pins the route to `/(creator)/submit/[applicationId]`
38	// (design.md §3.1 line 153 lists an alternate nested path, but the
39	// story AC wins per Ralph convention when the two disagree).
40	//
41	// Client-side preview via TikTok oEmbed (docs/tech-architecture.md §3h)
42	// is a UX nicety — the server re-classifies + re-fetches on submit so
43	// a missing preview never blocks and a present preview never bypasses
44	// server validation. Instagram URLs classify but skip the oembed call
45	// because the Meta Graph endpoint needs an app-token we don't ship in
46	// the bundle.
47	//
48	// Checklist semantics (design.md §2 line 608): mode='self' composer is
49	// two-state ☐/☑, every row starts unchecked, Submit is disabled until
50	// every row is checked + URL is a valid TikTok/Instagram shape. The
51	// server-side INCOMPLETE_AFFIRMATIONS gate is the source of truth; the
52	// client gate mirrors it for responsiveness. If the server surfaces
53	// missing ids anyway (e.g. a race where the listing's post-condition
54	// set changed), we surface a toast and stay put so the creator can
55	// re-check.
